Scheduled Guests

From the Infowars web site ::

On today's show, Alex talks with the executive director of Gun Owners of America, Larry Pratt, about the so-called "super-Congress" created under the debt deal that will be used to push through anti-Second Amendment legislation under the guise of stopping firearms from reaching the banker funded drug cartels in Mexico. 

Alex also talks with the presidential nominee of the Constitution Party for the 2008 U.S. Presidential election and founder-pastor of Crossroad Baptist Church in Pensacola, Florida, Chuck Baldwin, about his new book, Romans 13: The True Meaning of Submission.
